![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow)

</div>

---

## 📖 About

Dr. Ava is an AI-powered medical assistant that answers health-related questions by retrieving relevant passages from a knowledge base of medical PDF documents, then generating a grounded, empathetic response — instead of relying purely on an LLM's memory (which can hallucinate medical facts).

It's built using a **Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG)** pipeline:

```
User Question
     │
     ▼
Embed the question (MiniLM sentence embeddings)
     │
     ▼
Search FAISS vector store for the 3 most relevant document chunks
     │
     ▼
Inject those chunks as context into a prompt
     │
     ▼
LLM (Hugging Face hosted model) generates the answer
     │
     ▼
Response returned to the user (+ optional voice output)
```

> ⚠️ **Disclaimer:** Dr. Ava is an educational/demo project. It does not replace professional medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment. Always consult a qualified healthcare provider.

---

## ✨ Features

- 🔍 **Document-grounded answers** — responses are generated from a real medical knowledge base (PDFs you provide), not just the LLM's raw memory
- 🧠 **RAG pipeline** using LangChain + FAISS + Hugging Face embeddings
- 🗣️ **Text-to-speech** — converts responses to audio via `pyttsx3` so Dr. Ava can "speak" answers
- 🌐 **FastAPI backend** with a simple REST API (`/api/ask`, `/api/speak`)
- 🛟 **Graceful fallback mode** — if no Hugging Face token is configured, the app still runs and returns a clear message instead of crashing
- ☁️ **Vercel-ready** deployment config included

---

## 🧱 Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| Backend framework | FastAPI + Uvicorn |
| LLM orchestration | LangChain |
| Embeddings | `sentence-transformers/all-MiniLM-L6-v2` (Hugging Face) |
| Vector store | FAISS |
| LLM | Hugging Face Inference Endpoint (default: `HuggingFaceH4/zephyr-7b-beta`) |
| Text-to-speech | pyttsx3 |
| Deployment | Vercel |

---

## 📁 Project Structure

```
MEDICAL-CHATBOT19/
├── medical_chatbot.py          # Loads PDFs, chunks text, builds the FAISS vector store
├── connect_memory_with_llm.py  # Standalone script: query the vector store + LLM from the terminal
├── server.py                   # FastAPI app — serves the web UI and /api/ask, /api/speak endpoints
├── setup.py                    # One-command setup: installs deps, checks config, checks vector store
├── install_requirments.py      # Installs core Python dependencies
├── vercel.json                 # Vercel deployment configuration
├── data/                       # (you add this) — source PDF documents for the knowledge base
├── vectorstore/db_faiss/       # Generated FAISS index (created by medical_chatbot.py)
├── static/                     # Frontend files served at "/" (index.html, etc.)
└── .env                        # Environment variables (HF_TOKEN, HF_REPO_ID, PORT) — NEVER commit this
```

---

## ⚙️ Setup & Installation

### 1. Clone the repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/rajbaibhav1910/MEDICAL-CHATBOT19.git
cd MEDICAL-CHATBOT19
```

### 2. Create a virtual environment
```bash
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate      # On Windows: venv\Scripts\activate
```

### 3. Install dependencies
```bash
python install_requirments.py
```

### 4. Configure your environment variables
Create a `.env` file in the project root:
```
HF_TOKEN=your_huggingface_token_here
HF_REPO_ID=HuggingFaceH4/zephyr-7b-beta
PORT=8000
```
Get a free token at [huggingface.co/settings/tokens](https://huggingface.co/settings/tokens).

> 🔒 **Never commit your `.env` file.** Make sure it's listed in `.gitignore`.

### 5. Add your medical knowledge base
Place your source PDF documents inside a `data/` folder in the project root.

### 6. Build the vector store
```bash
python medical_chatbot.py
```
This reads all PDFs in `data/`, splits them into chunks, embeds them, and saves the FAISS index to `vectorstore/db_faiss/`.

### 7. Run the server
```bash
python server.py
```
Then open **http://localhost:8000** in your browser.

---

## 🔌 API Reference

### `POST /api/ask`
Ask a medical question.

**Request body:**
```json
{ "question": "What are common symptoms of diabetes?" }
```

**Response:**
```json
{ "answer": "..." }
```

### `POST /api/speak`
Convert a text response to speech (returns WAV audio).

**Request body:**
```json
{ "text": "Some text to convert to speech" }
```

---

## ☁️ Deployment (Vercel)

This project includes a `vercel.json` already configured to deploy `server.py` as a serverless function and serve the `static/` folder directly.

1. Push your code to GitHub
2. Import the repo into [Vercel](https://vercel.com)
3. Add `HF_TOKEN` and `HF_REPO_ID` as environment variables in the Vercel project settings (never in code)
4. Deploy

